puberty in males (testicular development) and females (breast development) can be defined using established clinical criteria that are more than two standard deviations above the mean age of pubertal onset in the general population.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the age thresholds?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["12 and 12","13 and 13","13 and 14","14 and 13","14 and 14"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct age thresholds for diagnosing delayed puberty are \u003Cstrong\u003E14 years for males (testicular development) and 13 years for females (breast development)\u003C/strong\u003E. These represent established clinical criteria that are more than two standard deviations above the mean age of pubertal onset in the general population.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe other combinations are incorrect:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E13 and 14\u003C/strong\u003E - This reverses the correct ages for males and females\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E14 and 14\u003C/strong\u003E - This incorrectly suggests the same age threshold for both sexes\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E13 and 13\u003C/strong\u003E - This threshold is too early for males and correct for females\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E12 and 12\u003C/strong\u003E - These thresholds are too early for both sexes\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn males, the first sign of puberty is testicular enlargement (\u0026gt;4 mL volume or \u0026gt;2.5 cm length). In females, the first sign is breast development (thelarche). These milestones typically occur earlier in females than males, which is reflected in the different diagnostic thresholds.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Delayed puberty in males is defined as absence of testicular enlargement by age 14 years.","Delayed puberty in females is defined as absence of breast development by age 13 years."],"references":["Zhu J, Chan YM. Adult Consequences of Self-Limited Delayed Puberty. Pediatrics. 2017 Jun;139(6):e20163177. doi: 10.1542/peds.2016-3177. Epub 2017 May 18. PMID: 28562264; PMCID: PMC8579478.","Mohanraj S, Prasad HK. Delayed Puberty. Indian J Pediatr. 2023 Jun;90(6):590-597. doi: 10.1007/s12098-023-04577-x. Epub 2023 May 2. PMID: 37127825.","Harrington J, Palmert MR. An Approach to the Patient With Delayed Puberty. J Clin Endocrinol Metab. 2022 May 17;107(6):1739-1750. doi: 10.1210/clinem/dgac054. PMID: 35100608.","Lissauer, T., \u0026 Carroll, W. (Eds.). (2021). Illustrated Textbook of Paediatrics E-Book: Illustrated Textbook of Paediatrics E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52433"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16274"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52433","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/52433"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-03T09:33:45+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-03T09:34:29+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8965"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66979"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"9","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/9"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc76","name":"Paediatrics","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-01-16T08:39:03+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relat